<td valign=top> 
<b> Animation </b>
<BR>
<p>
We are interested in finding low-dimensional representations of
complex human motions.  For example, each frame of the 3-D motion
sequence shown to the right can be described by a 36-dimensional
vector (12 joints, each with X,Y,Z values).  

<BR><BR>

We have been developing computational techniques for reducing the
dimensionality of this data into a lower and perceptually meaningful
space.  In this example, we are able to find a one-dimensional
representation that corresponds to the inherent one-dimensional nature
of the motion.

<BR><BR>

<i>(Collaborative work with Fred Henle and <a
href="http://www.cs.duke.edu/~brd"> Bruce Donald</a>)</i>

